servings: 2
course: main course
---

Preheat your oven to 200 degrees. Drizzle some @olive oil{} on a #baking tray{} and pop in your oven to get hot. Boil your kettle.

> This will give your salmon a lovely crispy skin!

Cut the @onion{1} in half through the root, peel and chop into roughly ½cm pieces. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{} if you have one). Put a #saucepan{} on medium heat with a drizzle of oil and add your onion. Cook for ~{5%minutes} or until your onion is soft, then add your garlic and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Add the @freekeh{100%g} along with the @vegetable stock pot{1/2}. Pour in the @water{200%ml}. Bring to a simmer, then reduce the heat to low, cover the pan with a #lid{} and leave to cook gently for ~{15%minutes}. Once your freekeh has been cooking for 15 mins, take the pan off the heat and add the @baby spinach{1%bag}. Put the lid back on and leave to the side for ~{5%minutes} more.

In the meantime, put the @chermoula spice mix{1%packet} in a #bowl{} with the @olive oil{2%tbsp}. Stir together, then add the @salmon fillet{2} and mix around with your hands to make sure it is well coated.

Take your hot baking tray out of your oven (carefully!), and gently lay your salmon skin-side down. Season each salmon fillet with a pinch of @salt{} and a good grind of @black pepper{} and pop in your oven on the top shelf for ~{10-12%minutes}.

> The salmon is cooked when flaky and opaque all the way through.

While your freekeh and salmon cook, put a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. While the pan gets hot, roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1%bunch}. Once the pan is hot, add the @sesame seeds{15%g} and dry-fry for ~{1-2%minutes} until golden. Remove them from the pan.

> Watch the sesame seeds don't burn!

When your freekeh has rested for 5 mins, take the lid off, add half your parsley and stir well. This is your pilaf. Taste and add more salt and pepper if necessary.

Serve your pilaf in #bowls{} with your salmon placed on top, a sprinkling of sesame seeds and your remaining parsley. Squeeze over some @lemon{1/2%lemon}(juiced) and enjoy!